Implemented the first-stage graphics facade refactor.

What changed:
- `IRenderPass` now takes/stores `Graphics&` instead of `IDeviceManager&` in [common.h](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/core/graphics/common.h):4004.
- Removed public `Graphics::getDeviceManager()` and added facade methods for render-pass registration, backbuffer/framebuffer access, window title/state, and input forwarding in [graphics.h](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/core/graphics/graphics.h):92 and [graphics.cpp](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/core/graphics/graphics.cpp):137.
- `RendererSystem` now binds to `IRenderPass(graphics)` and queries the current backbuffer through `Graphics` in [renderer_system.cpp](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/impl/ecs_graphics/renderer_system.cpp):160.
- Project world setup/teardown registers render passes through `Graphics` in [project_entry.cpp](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/loader/project_entry.cpp):47.
- X11, Wayland, and Win frame/input forwarding now call `Graphics` directly, for example [frame_linux_x11.cpp](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/core/frame/frame_linux_x11.cpp):353, [frame_linux_wayland.cpp](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/core/frame/frame_linux_wayland.cpp):651, and [frame_win.cpp](/home/limstudio/WorkStation/NWBLot/core/frame/frame_win.cpp):201.

The manager still exists internally as the Vulkan/device/presentation coordinator, but external app/framework code no longer reaches through `Graphics -> DeviceManager` for those operations. The only remaining direct manager calls are inside `Graphics` itself.

